    <p>Hu­man­ity has been plagued with an on­slaught of ex­treme weather events in re­cent years, from hur­ri­canes to wild­fires.</p>
    <p>Can each one be linked to cli­mate change? To find out more,</p>
    <p>ST’s en­vi­ron­ment cor­re­spon­dent Au­drey Tan and cli­mate change ed­i­tor David Fog­a­rty speak with cli­mate sci­en­tist Friederike</p>
    <p>Otto, the co-lead of World Weather At­tri­bu­tion, on the in­ter­na­tional ef­fort to an­a­lyse and com­mu­ni­cate the pos­si­ble in­flu­ence of cli­mate change on ex­treme weather events.</p>
    <p>Find out more by scan­ning this episode us­ing our QR code.</p>

